                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>The Goldwater scholarship will help her achieve her goal of becoming a “full-time principal investigator,” she said, giving her the opportunity to study how cells can interact with bio-materials.</p>
<p>“I want to be a research scientist at a university," Xu said. "Because I’m so focused on patient care, having the additional medical degree will help me to contextualize my research better."</p>
<p>She added that she would not have gotten the scholarship without the help and support she has received at Duke. </p>
<p>Two additional Duke students&mdash;Dev Dabke and Reena Debray&mdash;were named among the 307 honorable mentions for the award.</p>
